title: Pregnant women in England at ‘growing risk’ of serious injury in childbirth
summary: NHS data reveals a 16% rise in the incidence of third- and fourth-degree perineal tears among mothers since 2020. This increase highlights growing concerns regarding childbirth injuries. The findings may prompt further investigation into maternal care practices.

title: Hamas’s aim to retain authority in Gaza involves keeping the guns
summary: Amid a ceasefire lacking legal order or alternative governance, the group is resorting to violence to intimidate competitors. This power vacuum has led to escalating tensions and unrest. Effective measures to restore stability are urgently needed.

title: Wood burning and gas cooking hugely costly to healthcare systems, New Zealand study finds
summary: Experts recommend switching from gas hobs to electric alternatives, highlighting benefits for both public health and environmental sustainability. This transition could reduce harmful emissions and improve indoor air quality. The proposed change is seen as a positive step towards fighting climate change while promoting safer cooking conditions.

title: Millennial dads are experiencing something mums have known for a long time | Gaby Hinsliff
summary: Guardian columnist Gaby Hinsliff highlights that many men aspire to be active, involved parents. However, they are struggling to balance the conflicting demands of family responsibilities and work commitments. This tension is causing distress for many fathers who wish to engage more fully in their children's lives.
